## 5. NON-NEGOTIABLE CODING CONVENTIONS

These have bitten the project before. Violating them costs hours.

### React imports

```js
// CORRECT
import { useState, useEffect } from "react"
function App() { ... }
export default App

// WRONG — produces "_react2 is not defined" build errors
import React, { useState } from "react"
export default function App() { ... }
```

The artifact renderer breaks on the wrong pattern. ALWAYS named imports from "react", ALWAYS function declarations, ALWAYS `export default App` on its own line at file bottom.

### File structure

- `src/App.jsx` — main app (single file, large, will refactor later)
- `src/main.jsx` — entry point with `<BrowserRouter>` wrapping `<App />`
- `public/` — static assets (favicon.svg, og-image.svg)
- `index.html` — root HTML, contains OG meta tags

### No new dependencies without justification

Stack is React + Vite + Supabase + react-router-dom. Don't add UI libraries (Material UI, Chakra, etc.), animation libraries (Framer Motion, etc.), or CSS frameworks (Tailwind isn't installed). Plain CSS and inline styles are the convention.

### Commit conventions

- One logical change per commit
- Format: `Sprint N (X/Y): {short description}`
- Push after every commit (stream timeout protection)
- Branch naming: `claude/sprint-{N}-pr-{P}-{theme}` e.g. `claude/sprint-2-pr-2-calendar-editing`

### Stream timeout discipline

Claude Code on the web has a known stream idle timeout bug. Mitigation:

- Commit and push after every sub-step
- Don't batch 10 changes into one massive response
- If a chunk is taking long, pause and ask Khalid for "go" between sub-steps
- If you hit "API Error: Stream idle timeout - partial response received": commit what you have if you can, tell Khalid which sub-step you stopped at, wait for restart instruction

