## 7. KEY ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS (the things you'd otherwise have to ask)

### Public visibility
All pages are public-with-link by default. No private/listed toggle yet. That's Sprint 4+ (tied to marketplace launch).

### Mobile rendering
Below 768px viewport = single-column vertical stack ordered by y then x of each block on desktop. Drag DISABLED on mobile entirely. Tap a block → action sheet (delete/edit/style/up/down). NO mobile-specific layouts — same blocks, different rendering.

### Templates
Copied at save-time, not referenced. Template updates do NOT propagate to existing pages. Critical for marketplace integrity (buyer's purchase is a frozen snapshot).

### Marketplace (when built)
- Sellable layouts contain **structure only** (block positions, sizes, rotations, colors, fonts, embed slots)
- NOT content (text, images, embeds, calendar entries, journal data)
- Default opt-in OFF per save (must be explicitly enabled per save)
- $8.99 floor, 15% platform fee
- Anyone can sell, every page can be sold (open supply)
- Discovery via feeds + curated badges, NOT search/categories

### Authentication
Supabase native email + password only currently. OAuth (Google/Apple) and magic links not wired. Email verification currently OFF — turn on before public launch.

### Mobile detection
`useIsMobile()` hook reading `window.matchMedia('(max-width: 767px)')`. NEVER user-agent sniffing.

### URLs
- `/` — home (start screen for visitors, own page for logged-in users)
- `/u/{handle}` — public read-only view of user's active page
- `/u/{handle}/edit` — owner-only edit view (redirects to `/` if logged out, to `/u/{handle}` if wrong user)
- `/account` — settings page (Sprint 2)

### URL format note
Current: `koy-calendar-ecek.vercel.app/u/{handle}`. Real domain TBD before public launch. Khalid's roadmap includes custom domain support as a Pro upsell (`yourname.com` → their Koy page).

